## Facilitation Tips

1. **Start with the "why"** — connect each concept to a real problem
2. **Alternate between tracks** — Product Development and New Process Design examples
3. **Use software live** — demonstrate statistical tools in real-time
4. **Check for understanding** — quick polls after each major concept
5. **Pace for exercises** — circulate and identify struggling students early

## Common Issues and Resolutions

| Issue | Resolution |
|-------|------------|
| Software not installed | Use cloud-based Minitab Express or RStudio Cloud |
| Students falling behind | Pair struggling students with advanced peers |
| Exercise data errors | Provide pre-loaded datasets and verify checksums |
| Time running short | Prioritize guided exercise over independent practice |

